plastic_bottle.instructions: Remove cap and label, rinse container. Place in blue recycling bin.
plastic_bottle.tips: Check your municipal recycling program - guidelines vary by province.

ON.instructions: Empty and rinse. Blue bin collection every other week in most municipalities.

BC.instructions: Return to depot or curbside collection. Part of BC's Extended Producer Responsibility program.

QC.instructions: Vider et rincer. Placer dans le bac de recyclage selon les directives municipales.

glass_bottle.instructions: Remove cap and labels. Many provinces have bottle deposit programs.
glass_bottle.tips: Check for deposit symbols - return to beer/liquor stores for refund where applicable.

aluminum_can.instructions: Empty and rinse. Most provinces include in curbside recycling programs.
aluminum_can.tips: Alberta has beverage container deposit program - return for 5-25Â¢ refund.

paper_cup.instructions: Most paper cups have plastic lining - dispose in regular garbage.
paper_cup.tips: Some municipalities accept in organics if certified compostable.

food_waste.instructions: Place in green bin organics program where available.
food_waste.tips: Composting programs vary - check if your municipality has curbside organics collection.

electronic_device.instructions: Take to municipal hazardous waste depot or manufacturer take-back program.
electronic_device.tips: Many provinces have Extended Producer Responsibility for electronics.

battery.instructions: Return to collection points at retailers or municipal facilities.
battery.tips: Call2Recycle program accepts household batteries at many locations across Canada.

tim_hortons_cup.instructions: Tim Hortons cups are not recyclable in most programs - dispose in garbage.
tim_hortons_cup.tips: Bring a reusable cup for environmental impact reduction and potential discount.

cardboard_box.instructions: Flatten and remove tape/staples. Place in recycling bin.
cardboard_box.tips: Cardboard is widely accepted in municipal recycling programs across Canada.

plastic_bag.instructions: Take to grocery store collection bins - not accepted in curbside recycling.
plastic_bag.tips: Loblaws, Metro, and other retailers have plastic bag collection programs.

milk_carton.instructions: Empty and rinse. Most provinces accept in curbside recycling.
milk_carton.tips: Tetra Pak cartons are recyclable at specialized facilities in most regions.
